WEBVTT

00:01.580 --> 00:04.660
♪ ♪

00:17.660 --> 00:18.750
What are we doing?

00:18.750 --> 00:20.870
It's Christmastime.

00:28.580 --> 00:31.410
WOMAN:Tell me if this stings.

00:32.950 --> 00:34.330
Yeah, it stings.

00:34.330 --> 00:35.200
Good.

00:35.200 --> 00:36.290
Not expired.

00:36.290 --> 00:38.000
So, what happened?

00:38.000 --> 00:39.000
Same as every day.

00:39.000 --> 00:41.500
Tomas and his dumbass crew
gave me crap

00:41.500 --> 00:43.660
'cause I don't know
the language yet.

00:43.660 --> 00:44.700
I just hate it here.

00:44.700 --> 00:47.450
Remember you said
the same thing in Cairo?

00:47.450 --> 00:49.500
And before that, in Athens.

00:49.500 --> 00:51.450
Ten bucks says,
by next Christmas,

00:51.450 --> 00:54.120
you and Tomas
will be best friends.

00:54.120 --> 00:56.700
Ow.
Oh, sorry.
That one's deep.

00:56.700 --> 00:59.000
Ow.
Okay, just hold still, baby.

00:59.000 --> 01:00.200
Close your eyes.

01:00.200 --> 01:00.950
If you could be

01:00.950 --> 01:04.700
anywhere in the world right now,
where would you want to be?

01:04.700 --> 01:06.750
Armenia.

01:06.750 --> 01:08.580
I liked Armenia.

01:08.580 --> 01:09.330
Okay, so...

01:09.330 --> 01:12.410
picture the mountains
above Jermuk.

01:12.410 --> 01:14.500
There's two feet
of fresh snow.

01:14.500 --> 01:16.660
You're skiing
from hot spring

01:16.660 --> 01:20.000
to hot spring.

01:20.000 --> 01:21.160
There.

01:21.160 --> 01:22.330
Done.

01:22.330 --> 01:23.500
Better?

01:23.500 --> 01:24.700
Yeah.

01:24.700 --> 01:26.700
Put on the hat.

01:26.700 --> 01:27.870
What?

01:27.870 --> 01:29.330
Every year. Why?

01:29.330 --> 01:31.700
It's a Cole family tradition.

01:31.700 --> 01:33.870
'Cause some memories

01:33.870 --> 01:36.700
are worth holding on to.

01:41.040 --> 01:41.450
Aw, you blinked.

01:41.450 --> 01:44.200
Gonna try another one.
We already did

01:44.200 --> 01:44.580
another one.

01:44.580 --> 01:46.830
Why do we have
to keep doing this?

01:46.830 --> 01:47.830
Cole family tradition.

01:47.830 --> 01:50.040
Some memories
are worth holding on to.

01:50.040 --> 01:51.330
I thought
the Cole family tradition

01:51.330 --> 01:56.040
was a phone call each Christmas
from a different war zone.

01:56.750 --> 01:58.040
Well...

01:58.040 --> 02:01.080
this is a year
of new traditions.

02:01.080 --> 02:02.200
I'm here.

02:02.200 --> 02:04.500
Your mom's engaged.

02:05.450 --> 02:07.040
You're not sorry you're...

02:07.040 --> 02:11.370
not celebrating Christmas
with Andrew's parents, are you?

02:11.370 --> 02:11.830
Are you kidding?

02:11.830 --> 02:14.250
They live on a golf course
in San Diego.

02:14.250 --> 02:17.910
That's basically, like,
a retirement community.

02:18.660 --> 02:19.910
Okay, here's the plan.

02:19.910 --> 02:20.870
We're gonna have a Christmas

02:20.870 --> 02:23.410
that makes up
for all the ones that I missed.

02:23.410 --> 02:27.080
It's gonna be
the best Christmas ever.

02:27.080 --> 02:28.660
You don't have to say that.

02:28.660 --> 02:32.700
Mom told me to keep
my expectations low.

02:32.700 --> 02:33.500
So...

02:33.500 --> 02:35.700
Okay. Well, I'm doubling down.

02:35.700 --> 02:38.700
Best Christmas ever.

02:44.330 --> 02:46.080
Hey, buddy.
Cool flippers.

02:46.080 --> 02:48.120
I think Jacques Cousteau's
here to see you.

02:48.120 --> 02:49.370
Hey, Sam.

02:49.370 --> 02:51.160
Are you coming?
My dad chucked

02:51.160 --> 02:53.370
a bunch of quarters
into the deep end.

02:53.370 --> 02:55.540
Dad, can I go swimming already?

02:55.540 --> 02:56.370
Yeah, of course.

02:56.370 --> 02:58.370
After one more picture.

02:58.830 --> 03:01.540
:
Here we go.

03:03.830 --> 03:05.410
All right.

03:11.040 --> 03:12.200
I'm loving it, man.

03:12.200 --> 03:12.750
I'm there six weeks,

03:12.750 --> 03:15.660
and they already put me in
charge of tires and brake pads.

03:15.660 --> 03:17.790
It's just a matter of time
before they name you

03:17.790 --> 03:19.660
the third Pep Boy.

03:19.660 --> 03:22.790
OSCAR:
Yeah, my parole officer's happy

03:22.790 --> 03:23.160
about it.

03:23.160 --> 03:25.080
Sam and I will be able
to move out

03:25.080 --> 03:25.700
of this place pretty soon.

03:25.700 --> 03:29.160
Well, you got to make sure
you come say goodbye first.

03:29.160 --> 03:31.040
We're gonna miss you guys.

03:31.040 --> 03:32.200
Well, it won't be for a while.

03:32.200 --> 03:34.000
I mean, I got to save
some more money.

03:34.000 --> 03:37.910
Can't even afford to buy this
guy Christmas gifts right now.

03:37.910 --> 03:40.290
(vehicle approaching,
hip

03:42.370 --> 03:44.250
Hey, this is a
guy from work.

03:44.250 --> 03:46.330
You mind keeping
an eye on Sam for me?

03:46.330 --> 03:48.540
Yeah, 'course.

04:06.540 --> 04:08.450
MURTAUGH:Did you pack?

04:08.450 --> 04:10.080
How are you getting
to the airport?

04:10.080 --> 04:10.830
RJ:
Uh, I think

04:10.830 --> 04:13.200
there's a bus from downtown.
Don't think.

04:13.200 --> 04:14.370
And don't take the bus.

04:14.370 --> 04:15.620
Take a cab. We'll pay for it.

04:15.620 --> 04:16.910
It's RJ. Look. It's your mother.
Hi.

04:16.910 --> 04:18.330
Yup, Dad, we can see him. Yup.
Say hi.

04:18.330 --> 04:20.080
Well, give it to me
when you're done.

04:20.080 --> 04:20.620
Yeah.
Oh, RJ,

04:20.620 --> 04:22.160
bring back Costa Rica T-shirts,
please.

04:22.160 --> 04:23.000
MURTAUGH:
Hey, did you,

04:23.000 --> 04:25.120
um, print out your
boarding pass?

04:25.120 --> 04:28.120
Yeah, yeah. I-I printed
my boarding pass. I'm good.

04:28.120 --> 04:28.830
Don't just open up the e-mail.

04:28.830 --> 04:31.040
You have to print it.
He just said he printed it.

04:31.040 --> 04:33.200
Okay, and when is
your return flight?

04:33.200 --> 04:35.000
Uh, I don't know.
I haven't booked it.

04:35.000 --> 04:37.870
Um, I was gonna do that
when I got home.

04:37.870 --> 04:38.540
Okay.

04:38.540 --> 04:39.790
That's-that's a good idea, son.

04:39.790 --> 04:43.950
All right. Love you,
and I will see you tomorrow.

04:44.370 --> 04:45.290
Did you hear that?

04:45.290 --> 04:47.660
The part where you
didn't hand me the phone?

04:47.660 --> 04:48.620
No. The return flight.

04:48.620 --> 04:51.790
He didn't make one. Maybe
he's given up on Costa Rica,

04:51.790 --> 04:54.330
and maybe
we can convince him to stay.

04:54.330 --> 04:56.750
Baby, we can't convince RJ
to do anything.

04:56.750 --> 04:59.450
It is not our job.
He is an adu...
Yes, it is.

04:59.450 --> 05:00.870
No, it's not.
It is.

05:00.870 --> 05:02.290
Roger, he's an adult.

05:02.290 --> 05:03.910
But that gives
me an idea.

05:03.910 --> 05:06.160
Hmm?
We can do a family dinner.

05:06.160 --> 05:08.120
Family dinner?
No, we got to go bigger.

05:08.120 --> 05:10.080
I'm thinking a partay.

05:10.080 --> 05:10.910
A partay?
Yes.

05:10.910 --> 05:12.370
Roger, I don't kn...
With the get down,

05:12.370 --> 05:13.910
like the kids are doing.
Oh, my gosh.

05:13.910 --> 05:15.290
No.
Uh... Wait, seriously?

05:15.290 --> 05:16.830
A partay
for coming home?

05:16.830 --> 05:19.540
I'm here all the time.
Yeah, and we'll have

05:19.540 --> 05:21.620
a party for you
when you're 35 years old

05:21.620 --> 05:24.200
and married to the guy
that we both approve.

05:24.200 --> 05:25.620
Thank you.
In the meantime,

05:25.620 --> 05:29.950
let's make this a night
that RJ remembers.

05:29.950 --> 05:31.620
Okay. Fine.

05:31.620 --> 05:32.700
Fine.

05:32.700 --> 05:33.910
A small party.

05:33.910 --> 05:34.660
Yes.
Okay?

05:34.660 --> 05:38.410
Okay. Wh... You act
like I'm gonna go overboard.

05:46.040 --> 05:47.370
:
Alan,

05:47.370 --> 05:48.950
I heard something downstairs.

05:48.950 --> 05:51.080
Probably just
the house settling.

05:51.080 --> 05:52.910
That's not a real thing.
Go look.

05:52.910 --> 05:56.000
(clattering, shattering
in distance)

05:57.700 --> 05:58.830
I'm calling 911.

05:58.830 --> 06:00.330
Screw that.

06:02.330 --> 06:03.290
Sorry, hon,

06:03.290 --> 06:06.370
you're getting
your Christmas present early.

06:06.910 --> 06:09.620
You got me a shotgun
for Christmas?

06:09.620 --> 06:12.870
You always return
the sweaters.

06:17.620 --> 06:19.120
Nobody move!

06:32.790 --> 06:35.250
Those firearm lessons
really paid off.

06:35.250 --> 06:36.330
I mean, who knew?

06:36.330 --> 06:37.700
I'm assuming you have
a permit for that thing.

06:37.700 --> 06:39.290
Yeah, she does. A permit
to splatter a guy

06:39.290 --> 06:42.080
all over our Christmas tree
and soak all the ornaments.

06:42.080 --> 06:43.290
BRENDA:
Okay, Doc, let's go.

06:43.290 --> 06:46.120
You've got teeth
to straighten.

06:46.120 --> 06:47.540
Are you okay, Roger?

06:47.540 --> 06:49.450
You're very quiet
this morning.

06:49.450 --> 06:51.330
Very banter-free.

06:51.330 --> 06:52.370
Yeah, me, I'm good.

06:52.370 --> 06:53.410
Just a little pensive.

06:53.410 --> 06:55.750
You know, thinking about things,
things like...

06:55.750 --> 06:59.450
how hard is it for you
to RSVP to a party

06:59.450 --> 07:00.950
to which you were invited?

07:00.950 --> 07:02.910
Roger, did you invite me
to a party?

07:02.910 --> 07:04.200
Yeah, don't.
It's digital,

07:04.200 --> 07:06.040
which means I know you read it.

07:06.040 --> 07:07.790
I know when you read it.

07:07.790 --> 07:09.120
Early this morning.

07:09.120 --> 07:10.870
Oh. That party.

07:10.870 --> 07:12.700
Yeah, that party.
Yeah.

07:12.700 --> 07:13.450
Yeah, I can't make that.

07:13.450 --> 07:16.540
It's my first holiday
season with Maya.

07:16.540 --> 07:17.160
So bring her.

07:17.160 --> 07:19.950
There's a space
on the RSVP for guests.

07:19.950 --> 07:21.410
Just that one click,

07:21.410 --> 07:23.750
and I get that satisfying ding.

07:23.750 --> 07:26.370
Like that.

07:28.040 --> 07:29.580
Scorsese.

07:29.580 --> 07:30.580
Plus four?!

07:30.580 --> 07:31.540
W... I don't know exactly

07:31.540 --> 07:33.500
who they're gonna be yet.
Is that too many?

07:33.500 --> 07:35.700
You didn't cap off
the invite list.

07:35.700 --> 07:37.540
Do you mind if I...

07:37.540 --> 07:39.160
It is my favorite part, but...

07:39.160 --> 07:41.540
yeah.

07:44.910 --> 07:46.200
What is it?

07:46.200 --> 07:47.700
I'm giving you your RSVP.

07:47.700 --> 07:52.370
I'm not gonna be able to make it
to that party, Roger.

07:52.370 --> 07:55.200
♪♪

07:57.370 --> 07:59.250
AVERY:Three home invasions
in the last month,

07:59.250 --> 08:01.910
and you got him.
How is this not open

08:01.910 --> 08:03.750
You have your dead perp,
Lewis Fowler,

08:03.750 --> 08:04.870
and you know
who his partner is.

08:04.870 --> 08:06.660
Actually, we don't.
There's a lot of nuances here.

08:06.660 --> 08:09.870
Wait, you saw your dead home
invader conspiring yesterday

08:09.870 --> 08:11.200
at your hotel with an ex-con.

08:11.200 --> 08:13.040
"Conspiring"
is a loaded term.

08:13.040 --> 08:14.200
Oscar's a good man.

08:14.200 --> 08:14.620
He is an ex-con

08:14.620 --> 08:17.540
who literally did time
for breaking and entering.

08:17.540 --> 08:18.080
I know the guy.

08:18.080 --> 08:20.660
Our kids are friends.
He's turned his life around.

08:20.660 --> 08:22.700
Huh. And what does
your partner think?

08:22.700 --> 08:23.200
He thinks he did it.

08:23.200 --> 08:26.290
But, between us, Roger's
a little preoccupied

08:26.290 --> 08:28.040
with this party he's throwing.

08:28.040 --> 08:28.870
What party?

08:28.870 --> 08:30.080
He didn't invite me.

08:30.080 --> 08:31.750
Well, that's because
you and Todd go

08:31.750 --> 08:32.450
to Wyoming every Christmas

08:32.450 --> 08:35.000
to see his parents.
I'm sorry, is this Wyoming?

08:35.000 --> 08:37.750
Are we in Wyoming right now?

08:38.450 --> 08:39.160
No.

08:39.160 --> 08:40.330
It's not Wyoming.

08:40.330 --> 08:41.660
Are you okay, Captain?

08:41.660 --> 08:43.700
Everything good
with you and Todd?

08:43.700 --> 08:45.750
And now I'm being interrogated
about the status

08:45.750 --> 08:47.540
of my relationship
on Christmas Eve?

08:47.540 --> 08:48.750
That's perfect.

08:48.750 --> 08:49.120
Okay.

08:49.120 --> 08:53.160
So we'll, uh, just go
to the motel and talk to Oscar.

08:53.160 --> 08:53.290
Great.

08:53.290 --> 08:55.620
I'll let Roger know
you're in town for the holidays.

08:55.620 --> 08:57.040
Awesome.

08:57.040 --> 08:58.950
Okay.

09:07.040 --> 09:08.540
Ah, Detectives.

09:08.540 --> 09:09.620
It's a pre-Christmas miracle.

09:09.620 --> 09:13.750
Let me guess-- you guys heard
about my holiday cookies.

09:14.540 --> 09:16.370
We need to borrow your slab.

09:16.370 --> 09:17.160
What do we got?

09:17.160 --> 09:17.830
Chopped-up
body parts.

09:17.830 --> 09:19.910
A jogger found them
in Griffith Park.

09:19.910 --> 09:21.370
It's the holidays,
so, of course,

09:21.370 --> 09:22.910
Murtaugh and Cole catch
a simple case,

09:22.910 --> 09:24.910
and we get to spend
the day putting together

09:24.910 --> 09:25.700
some random guy's bits.

09:25.700 --> 09:28.160
The patriarchy strikes again.

09:28.160 --> 09:29.540
I think we got
the better gig.

09:29.540 --> 09:32.250
Come on, guys, we get
to make a puzzle

09:32.250 --> 09:34.040
out of body parts.

09:34.040 --> 09:36.620
You're kind of a weirdo,

09:36.620 --> 09:37.200
aren't you?

09:37.200 --> 09:40.120
Hey, you're both going
to Murtaugh's, right?

09:40.120 --> 09:42.450
Any interest
in a little pre

09:42.450 --> 09:45.500
I know this spicy,
spicy kombucha joint.

09:45.500 --> 09:46.620
Zero interest.

09:46.620 --> 09:47.660
I'm in.

09:47.660 --> 09:48.200
Cool.

09:48.200 --> 09:50.870
All right.
I'll text you the details.

09:51.580 --> 09:53.580
Ran out of gloves.

09:53.580 --> 09:55.120
Be right back.

09:56.540 --> 09:59.080
Just so you know, you don't
have to be polite to Scorsese.

09:59.080 --> 10:03.290
You'll want to, you know, shut
him down earlier in the day,

10:03.290 --> 10:04.330
before he gets his hopes up.

10:04.330 --> 10:06.410
Oh, I wasn't
gonna shut him down.

10:06.410 --> 10:08.580
I love kombucha.

10:08.580 --> 10:10.830
Everybody does.

10:10.830 --> 10:12.120
But it's Scorsese.

10:12.120 --> 10:13.040
So...

10:13.040 --> 10:14.410
Dude seems interesting.

10:14.410 --> 10:16.410
I keep forgetting
that you're new.

10:16.410 --> 10:18.870
Some people have
to learn the hard way.

10:18.870 --> 10:22.250
I like the hard way.

10:22.250 --> 10:24.080
MANAGER:Listen, the only reason

10:24.080 --> 10:26.450
I'm letting you guys in here
is 'cause of my respect

10:26.450 --> 10:28.080
and affection
for your partner.

10:28.080 --> 10:29.120
Also, we have
a warrant.

10:29.120 --> 10:30.080
Well, yeah,
you have that, too,

10:30.080 --> 10:31.200
but a lot of it's
'cause of the respect
Yeah.

10:31.200 --> 10:34.040
and affection
for your partner.
For the-for the partner. Yeah.

10:34.040 --> 10:35.290
Yeah.
Open the door.

10:35.290 --> 10:36.870
Okay. Yeah, yeah,
I can do that.

10:36.870 --> 10:38.290
I've got a magnetic personality.

10:38.290 --> 10:41.160
The Howard Hughes of this place.

10:41.160 --> 10:42.500
I am.

10:42.700 --> 10:44.000
Why don't you and the president

10:44.000 --> 10:45.200
of your fan club get started.

10:45.200 --> 10:47.410
I got to take this.

10:47.410 --> 10:49.040
Hey, baby.

10:49.040 --> 10:50.290
How you doing?
Roger,

10:50.290 --> 10:54.870
remember when you said we were
keeping RJ's party small?

10:54.870 --> 10:56.410
Now...

10:56.410 --> 10:58.500
did you order
an ice sculpture?

10:58.500 --> 11:00.950
:
Of course I didn't.

11:00.950 --> 11:02.000
Now, did I

11:02.000 --> 11:03.950
make a call and get a quote

11:03.950 --> 11:07.700
from a guy
for a ice sculpture? Uh...

11:07.700 --> 11:08.660
Ah... maybe.

11:08.660 --> 11:11.450
Roger, if you called just to get
a quote, why is the guy here?

11:11.450 --> 11:13.830
With a block of ice
and a chisel.

11:13.830 --> 11:15.620
And two DJs, Roger. Really?

11:15.620 --> 11:16.950
Two DJs?!

11:16.950 --> 11:18.200
I don't hear you.

11:18.200 --> 11:20.660
Baby, I'm gonna
have to call you back.

11:20.660 --> 11:21.040
Oscar Ripley?

11:21.040 --> 11:23.870
LAPD. We need to ta...

11:23.870 --> 11:25.540
Oh...

11:38.790 --> 11:41.200
Dad?
He's not gonna stop.

11:41.200 --> 11:43.330
Roger, don't shoot!

11:43.870 --> 11:45.870
Oscar, hit the brakes!

11:52.830 --> 11:54.750
MAYA:
Dad, your room.

11:54.750 --> 11:57.250
Don't worry, sweetie.
It's just a little mess,

11:57.250 --> 11:58.540
we'll clean it all up.
Get your hands

11:58.540 --> 12:02.790
behind your back.
Still gonna be the
best Christmas ever.

12:03.500 --> 12:05.200
Dad?

12:14.330 --> 12:15.620
It's not just the room.

12:16.620 --> 12:19.450
It's what was
in the room.

12:19.450 --> 12:21.000
Tree, decorations.

12:21.000 --> 12:24.870
I had these little
cute dancing elves.

12:24.870 --> 12:27.870
You just wind 'em up,
and they're...

12:28.160 --> 12:30.040
Not a single one survived.

12:30.040 --> 12:31.660
Look, I-I'm sorry, man.

12:31.660 --> 12:34.120
I truly am.
I panicked.

12:34.120 --> 12:36.160
Not a good look
on an innocent man.

12:36.160 --> 12:38.200
I heard about the burglary,
all right,

12:38.200 --> 12:40.080
and I knew
you saw me talking to Lewis.

12:40.080 --> 12:43.830
I was worried that you would
think I was involved.

12:44.620 --> 12:45.700
Guess what I think now.

12:45.700 --> 12:49.580
Lewis offered me the
job, but I said no.

12:49.580 --> 12:52.410
I got Sam to look after now.

12:52.410 --> 12:54.830
Speaking of which...

12:54.830 --> 12:55.500
Found this in your room.

12:55.500 --> 12:58.750
Stolen from a home invasion
last week.

12:58.750 --> 13:01.660
Oh, see, I bought that
off of Lewis.

13:01.660 --> 13:04.200
I'm just trying
to give Sam a great Christmas,

13:04.200 --> 13:08.200
especially since I've
missed so many already.

13:08.410 --> 13:10.620
I'm not the guy
you're looking for, Wes.

13:10.620 --> 13:13.790
Would you please tell Cole
that this is exactly the guy

13:13.790 --> 13:17.120
that we're looking for,
and we want to go home?

13:17.120 --> 13:18.500
Not me. I never
want to go home again.

13:18.500 --> 13:21.580
Okay, Mr. Dark and Stormy,
what's going on?

13:21.580 --> 13:24.330
Cole told me that you and Todd
cancelled your trip.
Not cancelled.

13:24.330 --> 13:28.790
Todd's in Wyoming. You know, I
don't want to talk about it.
Perfect, because I don't like...

13:28.790 --> 13:29.910
I mean, if he wants
to be apart

13:29.910 --> 13:30.830
for the holidays,
we'll be apart.

13:30.830 --> 13:33.200
Solo. Some people
find that peaceful.

