half-dozen mug books,

16:48.620 --> 16:51.120
and I found this.
Calvin Marks.

16:51.120 --> 16:53.330
Armed robbery, assault,

16:53.330 --> 16:54.000
home invasion.

16:54.000 --> 16:57.160
Plus, he shared a halfway
house with our DOA, Lewis.

16:57.160 --> 16:58.950
Look at the birthmark.

16:58.950 --> 17:01.200
Yeah.

17:01.450 --> 17:05.540
Okay, we got to be back here
by 8:00, all right?
Okay.

17:05.540 --> 17:08.370
And I drive.
Let's go.

17:14.120 --> 17:15.790
This is the last
known address.

17:15.790 --> 17:18.660
Looks like nobody's
been here in forever.

17:18.660 --> 17:21.370
Well, this thing
is bolted shut.

17:21.370 --> 17:23.910
No one's getting
through that door tonight.

17:23.910 --> 17:24.790
I have a pitch.

17:24.790 --> 17:27.290
We come back tomorrow
with some warrants

17:27.290 --> 17:30.040
and heavy machinery.

17:30.950 --> 17:33.000
Hey, Tarzan, where you going?

17:33.000 --> 17:35.790
Looking for another way in.

17:38.290 --> 17:43.620
Hey, Roger,
do you believe in miracles?

17:43.620 --> 17:45.000
Come on.
You've never heard of...

17:45.000 --> 17:46.540
A fictional character. Get...

17:46.540 --> 17:49.160
See you downstairs.

17:53.120 --> 17:57.290
Come on down, Rog.

17:57.290 --> 17:58.500
Piece of cake.

18:04.200 --> 18:05.910
Roger, what's happening?

18:11.160 --> 18:12.580
Piece of cake?

18:12.580 --> 18:13.750
I'm stuck.

18:13.750 --> 18:14.910
Get me out of here.

18:14.910 --> 18:17.620
All right, all right,
settle down.

18:17.620 --> 18:19.080
Come on!

18:19.080 --> 18:19.410
Come on.

18:19.410 --> 18:22.040
Maybe a piece of cake
was the problem.

18:22.790 --> 18:24.410
All right, you stay right here.

18:24.410 --> 18:25.160
I'll be right back, buddy.

18:25.160 --> 18:28.370
I'm gonna get some, uh, cooking
spray or something slippery

18:28.370 --> 18:29.330
to get you out of there.

18:29.330 --> 18:32.660
Where you going?!
Don't leave me here!

18:46.000 --> 18:49.160
Hey, Roger!

19:01.500 --> 19:03.200
Oh, boy.

19:29.910 --> 19:32.290
Oh! Cole!

19:47.580 --> 19:48.950
Huh.

19:48.950 --> 19:50.160
Cole,

19:50.160 --> 19:52.870
where did they go?!

19:52.870 --> 19:54.410
In a surprising turn of events,

19:54.410 --> 19:56.580
it looks like
the front door opens after all.

19:56.580 --> 20:01.830
You know you're not invited
to my party, right?

20:01.830 --> 20:03.870
Roger.

20:06.960 --> 20:08.590
COLE:We call the arraignment judge

20:08.590 --> 20:09.800
at home and tell him
to spring Oscar

20:09.800 --> 20:11.250
because we have
two better suspects.

20:11.250 --> 20:12.380
Except we don't, do we?

20:12.380 --> 20:14.250
No, I mean, technically,
we don't have them.

20:14.250 --> 20:15.340
Technically, that's
what we need.

20:15.340 --> 20:18.460
You have no... you have no
perps, you have no evidence.

20:18.460 --> 20:20.300
We have a thumb.
A human thumb.

20:20.300 --> 20:22.130
Right. The, uh,
missing digit,

20:22.130 --> 20:25.090
which, even if you did have it,
would prove what, again?

20:25.090 --> 20:26.050
I don't know.

20:26.050 --> 20:29.000
But the wrong guy's in jail,
Captain. I'm sure of it.

20:29.000 --> 20:30.090
You're probably right.

20:30.090 --> 20:31.800
But without suspects
or evidence,

20:31.800 --> 20:34.250
there is no way
he's getting released.

20:34.250 --> 20:37.630
I'm sorry, Cole.
Merry Christmas.

20:40.960 --> 20:42.460
We're gonna get him out.

20:42.460 --> 20:43.710
But not tonight.

20:43.710 --> 20:45.090
I did everything I could.

20:45.090 --> 20:45.590
Well, it wasn't enough.

20:45.590 --> 20:48.710
I promised Sam you would
get his Dad out by tomorrow.

20:48.710 --> 20:50.340
Honey, why would
you promise him that?

20:50.340 --> 20:51.250
Because I know what it's like

20:51.250 --> 20:53.250
to not have your dad there
for Christmas.

20:53.250 --> 20:54.920
I've done it my entire life,

20:54.920 --> 20:56.670
and it sucks.

20:56.670 --> 20:58.050
Maya.

20:58.050 --> 21:00.380
Let her go.

21:00.380 --> 21:01.340
This'll pass.

21:01.340 --> 21:04.460
I don't even have a place
for her to sleep tonight.

21:04.460 --> 21:05.880
Cole, come on.
You both will stay here.

21:05.880 --> 21:08.550
You go back to the motel,
get some of your stuff.

21:08.550 --> 21:11.670
She knows
you're doing your best.

21:11.670 --> 21:14.630
Maybe.

21:14.800 --> 21:17.380
Deep down, I know she's right.

21:17.380 --> 21:20.500
It's not enough.

21:23.750 --> 21:26.670
♪ ♪

21:28.130 --> 21:29.250
How's your body?

21:29.250 --> 21:30.630
The one in the morgue.

21:30.630 --> 21:32.710
The one you're...
piecing together.

21:32.710 --> 21:33.420
Has...

21:33.420 --> 21:37.210
Uh, well, we're up to the waist,
so we know it's a male.

21:38.130 --> 21:40.750
We should have all the DNA
by tomorrow.

21:40.750 --> 21:41.050
Mm. Mm. Mm.

21:41.050 --> 21:43.300
But, Cap, what do you think
about this?

21:43.300 --> 21:44.800
The Gute and Scorsese--
she says

21:44.800 --> 21:47.000
she's having fun
with him tonight.

21:47.380 --> 21:48.750
Fun. With Scorsese.

21:48.750 --> 21:50.750
It's easy
to misunderstand people.

21:50.750 --> 21:53.550
Wait, what am I
misunderstanding?

21:53.550 --> 21:54.920
We're flawed.

21:54.920 --> 21:56.170
We make mistakes,

21:56.170 --> 21:57.670
we push away
the people we love.

21:57.670 --> 22:00.880
We're not talking
about Scorsese anymore, are we?

22:00.880 --> 22:03.050
Todd wasn't disappointed in me.

22:03.050 --> 22:05.880
:
I was disappointed in myself.

22:05.880 --> 22:08.050
I think I've become
difficult to live with.

22:08.050 --> 22:11.090
Okay, you know what?
I'm gonna get you some coffee.

22:11.090 --> 22:12.840
That's probably a good idea.

22:16.800 --> 22:17.670
Hey.
Hey.

22:17.670 --> 22:19.590
Uh, Dad, listen...
You landed!

22:19.590 --> 22:21.250
Huh? Well, listen,
you're a little late,

22:21.250 --> 22:24.130
but you'll make up some time
on the freeway, right?

22:24.130 --> 22:27.170
No, no, I'm-I'm still
in, uh, Costa Rica.

22:27.170 --> 22:28.630
Say what

22:28.630 --> 22:29.590
Yeah, my-my, uh,

22:29.590 --> 22:31.840
airline ticket got,
uh, messed up.

22:31.840 --> 22:32.960
Just a technical glitch.

22:32.960 --> 22:35.210
A glitch?
What kind of glitch?

22:35.210 --> 22:36.550
Um, well, they had me...

22:36.550 --> 22:39.000
on a flight for yesterday
and-and not today,

22:39.000 --> 22:40.500
on account of the time zones.

22:40.500 --> 22:43.840
Time zones? It's a
one-hour difference.

22:43.840 --> 22:44.500
That's not technical.

22:44.500 --> 22:49.460
It sounds like a humanglitch,
one very specific human.

22:49.460 --> 22:50.050
It's RJ.

22:50.050 --> 22:52.590
Fool missed his flight.
This is so typical

22:52.590 --> 22:55.090
of him.
Dad, I'm still on the phone.

22:55.090 --> 22:57.550
Well, listen, it'll...
honey, it'll be fine.

22:57.550 --> 22:58.800
When's the next flight out?

22:58.800 --> 23:01.960
Maybe tomorrow, end of the week.

23:01.960 --> 23:02.420
Um...

23:02.420 --> 23:04.380
I'm not sure--
you know, flights are spotty.

23:04.380 --> 23:07.340
Sp... You know what's spotty?
You're spotty!

23:07.340 --> 23:07.840
And flaky!

23:07.840 --> 23:09.500
That's the perfect country
for you.

23:09.500 --> 23:12.170
Okay, i-it happens,
and you are not helping.

23:12.170 --> 23:14.840
Yeah, it happens to
thiskid, all the time.

23:14.840 --> 23:17.800
We got 40people downstairs.
What are we supposed

23:17.800 --> 23:20.670
to tell them, you can't make it
to your own party?

23:20.670 --> 23:23.670
A party

23:23.670 --> 23:24.420
This is ridiculous.

23:24.420 --> 23:27.090
Do I have to come down there
and fly you back myself?

23:27.090 --> 23:30.210
Wha...? I didn't call you
to get yelled at.

23:30.210 --> 23:31.340
Okay, give me the phone.

23:31.340 --> 23:33.920
RJ, honey, why don't
you look into...

23:33.920 --> 23:34.380
You know what?

23:34.380 --> 23:38.460
New rule: you can't go
to another foreign country

23:38.460 --> 23:40.340
until you can read the clock.

23:40.340 --> 23:41.750
Roger, stop it.

23:41.750 --> 23:42.420
I'm serious.

23:42.420 --> 23:44.380
Look, if this is
how you're gonna be,

23:44.380 --> 23:46.250
maybe I shouldn't
come back at all.

23:46.250 --> 23:48.460
Oh. Well, it's a moot point now,
isn't it?

23:48.460 --> 23:50.880
Because even if
you wanted to,

23:50.880 --> 23:53.460
your flight left yesterday!

23:56.800 --> 23:59.210
Hmm! Can you
believe that?

23:59.210 --> 24:00.210
He hung up on me.

24:00.210 --> 24:04.050
Oh. I can't believe
it took him that long.

24:04.050 --> 24:06.840
You act like, somehow,
this is my fault.

24:06.840 --> 24:10.250
Oh, there is
nosomehowabout it.

24:10.250 --> 24:12.710
Why do you
always do that?

24:12.710 --> 24:14.960
:
Why... do what?

24:14.960 --> 24:16.250
Try to control him.

24:16.250 --> 24:18.380
Give him no margin
for error.

24:18.380 --> 24:19.250
RJ is an adult.

24:19.250 --> 24:21.460
Well, then he needs
to act like one.

24:21.460 --> 24:22.800
Hmm.
He forgets

24:22.800 --> 24:23.840
to register his passport,

24:23.840 --> 24:26.130
then he books the wrong
flight coming back home,

24:26.130 --> 24:29.920
and now, to top it all off,
he's missing his party.

24:29.920 --> 24:33.210
Hisparty?
Hisparty.

24:33.210 --> 24:34.210
Hmm.

24:34.210 --> 24:36.420
This is your party.

24:38.380 --> 24:42.250
I wanted a nice
dinner with our son.

24:42.250 --> 24:43.750
But I got

24:43.750 --> 24:45.250
an ice sculpture

24:45.250 --> 24:48.800
and12 gallons of gazpacho.

24:48.800 --> 24:50.550
They had a sale.

24:50.550 --> 24:52.880
And why are you acting like

24:52.880 --> 24:53.630
it's my fault that

24:53.630 --> 24:54.920
he missed his...
Missed...

24:54.920 --> 24:57.300
his flight, Roger.

24:57.300 --> 24:58.550
That's all.

24:58.550 --> 25:01.340
You have got to find
a new gear for him.

25:01.340 --> 25:06.050
Because if you keep giving RJ
reasons not to come home...

25:06.050 --> 25:09.090
he won't come home.

25:35.800 --> 25:38.460
YOUNG COLE:Come on, we're gonna be late.

25:38.460 --> 25:41.920
Tomas said we decorate
the tree before dinner.

25:41.920 --> 25:43.380
I'm excited, too.

25:43.380 --> 25:45.880
I-I'll see you tomorrow.

25:47.550 --> 25:50.880
We're leaving again, aren't we?

25:52.300 --> 25:53.130
Indonesia.

25:53.130 --> 25:58.170
They've asked me to cover
a separatist uprising.

25:58.880 --> 25:59.840
This is good news.

25:59.840 --> 26:03.170
We're gonna be living
on the beach.

26:03.170 --> 26:03.670
When are we going?

26:03.670 --> 26:06.000
They want me there
Christmas morning,

26:06.000 --> 26:07.000
so, um...

26:07.000 --> 26:09.250
we leave tonight.

26:10.000 --> 26:14.210
Hey. We're gonna be
surfing at sunrise.

26:14.210 --> 26:15.090
I don't care.

26:15.090 --> 26:17.800
We're supposed to have Christmas
with Tomas's family.

26:17.800 --> 26:20.340
I don't want to wake up
somewhere new.

26:20.340 --> 26:21.840
So... you'll make
new friends.

26:21.840 --> 26:25.250
You know how long it took me
to make thesefriends?

26:25.250 --> 26:27.090
I don't want
to start over.

26:27.090 --> 26:29.710
I know that this
is disappointing,

26:29.710 --> 26:32.840
but you have to see
the bigger picture.

26:32.840 --> 26:34.880
We have never seen Indonesia,

26:34.880 --> 26:37.250
and it is gonna be awesome.

26:37.250 --> 26:38.880
I promise.

26:38.880 --> 26:41.000
What do I always tell you, huh?

26:41.000 --> 26:44.050
Another adventure awaits.

26:48.380 --> 26:49.000
Dude.

26:49.000 --> 26:51.460
I went to the mat
for you, man, but...

26:51.460 --> 26:53.880
owner's real mad
about the whole...

26:53.880 --> 26:55.880
car-in-the-hotel thing.

26:55.880 --> 26:57.210
He wants you out.

26:57.210 --> 26:59.210
He called you a chaos magnet.

26:59.210 --> 27:00.840
Yeah. I get that.

27:00.840 --> 27:01.170
I don't.

27:01.170 --> 27:03.920
Youdidn't drive your car
into the wall.

27:03.920 --> 27:05.590
You're the
victim here.

27:05.590 --> 27:07.960
Super badass victim.

27:07.960 --> 27:09.210
I mean...

27:09.210 --> 27:10.960
no room at the inn?

27:10.960 --> 27:12.670
On Christmas Eve?

27:12.670 --> 27:14.750
What have we become?

27:14.750 --> 27:16.170
Gus...

27:16.170 --> 27:18.670
don't worry, I'll be fine.

27:18.670 --> 27:20.210
Yeah, but...

27:20.210 --> 27:21.960
where are you gonna go?

27:21.960 --> 27:25.340
Another adventure awaits.

